34唱 1:3 The LORD is slow to anger and great in power, And the LORD will by no means leave [the guilty] unpunished. In whirlwind and storm is His way, And clouds are the dust beneath His feet.
34唱 1:4 He rebukes the sea and makes it dry; He dries up all the rivers. Bashan and Carmel wither; The blossoms of Lebanon wither.
34唱 1:5 Mountains quake because of Him, And the hills dissolve; Indeed the earth is upheaved by His presence, The world and all the inhabitants in it.
34唱 1:6 Who can stand before His indignation? Who can endure the burning of His anger? His wrath is poured out like fire, And the rocks are broken up by Him.
34唱 1:7 The LORD is good, A stronghold in the day of trouble, And He knows those who take refuge in Him.
34唱 1:8 But with an overflowing flood He will make a complete end of its site, And will pursue His enemies into darkness.
34唱 1:9 Whatever you devise against the LORD, He will make a complete end of it. Distress will not rise up twice.
34唱 1:10 Like tangled thorns, And like those who are drunken with their drink, They are consumed As stubble completely withered.
34唱 1:11 From you has gone forth One who plotted evil against the LORD, A wicked counselor.
