34唱 3:6 "I will throw filth on you And make you vile, And set you up as a spectacle.
34唱 3:7 "And it will come about that all who see you Will shrink from you and say, 'Nineveh is devastated! Who will grieve for her?' Where will I seek comforters for you?"
34唱 3:8 Are you better than No-amon, Which was situated by the waters of the Nile, With water surrounding her, Whose rampart [was] the sea, Whose wall [consisted] of the sea?
34唱 3:9 Ethiopia was [her] might, And Egypt too, without limits. Put and Lubim were among her helpers.
34唱 3:10 Yet she became an exile, She went into captivity; Also her small children were dashed to pieces At the head of every street; They cast lots for her honorable men, And all her great men were bound with fetters.
34唱 3:11 You too will become drunk, You will be hidden. You too will search for a refuge from the enemy.
34唱 3:12 All your fortifications are fig trees with ripe fruit-- When shaken, they fall into the eater's mouth.
34唱 3:13 Behold, your people are women in your midst! The gates of your land are opened wide to your enemies; Fire consumes your gate bars.
34唱 3:14 Draw for yourself water for the siege! Strengthen your fortifications! Go into the clay and tread the mortar! Take hold of the brick mold!
34唱 3:15 There fire will consume you, The sword will cut you down; It will consume you as the locust [does.] Multiply yourself like the creeping locust, Multiply yourself like the swarming locust.
34唱 3:16 You have increased your traders more than the stars of heaven-- The creeping locust strips and flies away.
34唱 3:17 Your guardsmen are like the swarming locust. Your marshals are like hordes of grasshoppers Settling in the stone walls on a cold day. The sun rises and they flee, And the place where they are is not known.
34唱 3:18 Your shepherds are sleeping, O king of Assyria; Your nobles are lying down. Your people are scattered on the mountains, And there is no one to regather [them.]
34唱 3:19 There is no relief for your breakdown, Your wound is incurable. All who hear about you Will clap [their] hands over you, For on whom has not your evil passed continually?
