35钦 2:17 "For the violence done to Lebanon will overwhelm you, And the devastation of [its] beasts by which you terrified them, Because of human bloodshed and violence done to the land, To the town and all its inhabitants.
35钦 2:18 "What profit is the idol when its maker has carved it, [Or] an image, a teacher of falsehood? For [its] maker trusts in his [own] handiwork When he fashions speechless idols.
35钦 2:19 "Woe to him who says to a [piece of] wood, 'Awake!' To a dumb stone, 'Arise!' [And] that is [your] teacher? Behold, it is overlaid with gold and silver, And there is no breath at all inside it.
35钦 2:20 "But the LORD is in His holy temple. Let all the earth be silent before Him."
35钦 3:1 A prayer of Habakkuk the prophet, according to Shigionoth.
